<div id="test_image">
	<%= link_to image_tag('Training/train_1.jpg'), '#' %>
</div>


<div id = "q1">
    <hr>
    <p>
    Would you <b>like to visit</b> this place?
    </p>
    <i>Please select <b>one</b> of the following options.</i>

    <div id="slider-Attractiveness"></div>
    <table style="width:100%">
        <tr>
            <td style="text-align:left" width="12.5%">Extremely unlikely</td>
            <td style="text-align:center" >Unlikely</td>
            <td style="text-align:center" width="25%">Neutral</td>
            <td style="text-align:center" width="25%">Likely</td>
            <td style="text-align:right" width="12.5%">Extremely likely</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
</div>

<div id="q2" hidden>
    <hr>
    <p>
    Are you <b>familiar</b> with this place?
      <label class="btn btn-default"><input type="radio" name="familiarity" value="yes">Yes</label>
      <label class="btn btn-default"><input type="radio" name="familiarity" value="no">No</label>
    </p>
    <i>Please answer yes if you are familiar with this place, otherwise answer no.</i>
</div>

<div id = "q3" hidden>
    <hr>
    <p>
    How <b>unique</b> is this place?
    </p>
    <i>Please select <b>one</b> of the following options.</i>

    <div id="slider-Uniqueness"></div>
    <table style="width:100%">
        <tr>
            <td style="text-align:left" width="12.5%">I frequently see something like this</td>
            <td style="text-align:center" >Ordinary</td>
            <td style="text-align:center" width="25%">Neutral</td>
            <td style="text-align:center" width="25%">Unique</td>
            <td style="text-align:right" width="12.5%">I've never seen anything like this</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
</div>

<div id="q4" hidden>
    <hr>
    <p>
    Do you consider this place <b>friendly</b>?
        <label class="btn btn-default"><input type="radio" name="friendliness" value="yes">Yes</label>
        <label class="btn btn-default"><input type="radio" name="friendliness" value="no">No</label>
    </p>
    <i>Please answer yes if you think this place is friendly for you, otherwise answer no.</i>
</div>

<div id="q5" hidden>
    <hr>
    <p>
    How does this place make you <b>feel</b>?
    </p>
    <i>To answer this, please <b>move the mouse pointer inside the box</b> which contains a face picture. The facial expression will change according to the pointerâ€™s position (for example, move it to the right to make the face happier). Click whenever the facial expression best matches your feeling.
</i>
    <div class="offset5">
        <div id="affectchanger_div" hidden><input type="button" id="affectchanger" style="width:100px" class="btn btn-default" value="Change"></div>
        <canvas id="affect" width="100px" height="100px" style="border:0; padding:0;">
        </canvas>
    </div>
</div>

<div id="golden_q" hidden>
</div>

<input id="options" value="Bicycle|Canal/River|Building" type="hidden" />
<input id="checkimage" value="1" type="hidden" />

<div class="buttons" id="next_btn" hidden>
<div><i>After you have answered all the questions, click Next. <br> You <b>cannot change</b> your answers after you click Next!</i></div><br>
<%= link_to "Next", ready_part1_path, class: "btn btn-large btn-primary" %></div>
